# Zephyrus GU605MY — Prevent white noise bursts by keeping audio PCI controller powered on
# The Intel HDA controller (8086:7e28, class 0x040300) powers down during PCI runtime PM,
# causing digital mic noise bursts when it wakes back up.
# This rule forces the controller to stay in D0.

SUBSYSTEM=="pci", ATTR{vendor}=="0x8086", ATTR{class}=="0x040300", ATTR{power/control}="on"
